Former NFL Assistant Coach Mike Heimerdinger Dies at Age 58

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-10-01T17:47:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-01/former-nfl-assistant-coach-mike-heimerdinger-dies-at-age-58.html
Mike Heimerdinger, a former assistant
coach for three National Football League teams, died yesterday
at the age of 58.  Heimerdinger died while in  Mexico  receiving cancer
treatment, according to the Tennessee Titans website. He was the
team’s offensive coordinator when diagnosed with cancer last
November.  “Mike was a good man that brought a great level of
dedication and professionalism to his job,” Titans General
Manager Mike Reinfeldt said in a statement. “He was brave in
his fight and showed such a commitment to the game.”  Heimerdinger was also an assistant with the  Denver Broncos ,
winning the Super Bowl following the 1997 and 1998 seasons, and
New York Jets during his career.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  